spanGrp.span: sinpa chara akheh ruwng sinnu chara akheh thocha jenu
had a boy and a girl
vachara hin to unsah lopa jenu
Her children loved her very much
atarang ki vapal cha je te
achim ma vanu hinto thocha ve
hangthi oh dahtung kama doh vati mo e
"Wake up How did you leave me? How?" she said and cried and cried.
How?" she said and cried and cried.
vachalanu to ahe le doh chechenu vata-vata-vata-vata nate
The daughter kept on coming and crying
dah lapunu nangte thocha mo kada te dali ivangle vati mo eh
"Why, old woman, I thought you've already died. Why are you coming back?"
vachalnu kung dali avang thu mo eh?
(Asking) his sister "Why did you come with her back?"
vahmi khol thung tingnal eh din chee choo nu
There are lots of earthworms inside her eyeholes.
vana khol thung tingnal eh kira so chee chou nu, din chee choo nu
Inside her ears there worms leaking out, lots of them.
dah lapunu peedal so-so dahli avang th- thu mo eh?
This old woman is so dirty, why did you come alone with her?
kanu nanu unsah lonu kavang thu ve
Since I love my... our mother, I came back with her.
vajal vaso dinu kavang thu cha va ve
I came back with her because she resurrected.
"Wake up and change", said. "The Gmelina tree has changed"
her son (said) "The Gmelina tree has changed"
As (she) was saying "Wake up and change"
(he) was saying "The Gmelina tree has changed."
pavung ahlija vada tol ja nate
vangle nu than thung ha hlu nu tho cha
went back to the grave and died
After that she never returned again.
vachapa tuwng kheh ing adal ahlija danite,
mi itho hin he ajal jeso
vakowng hrin pete so ivang jal hlo-hlo hrang varende,
might newly change the skin and resurrect,
the son said: the Gmelina tree has changed.
pavung thing heeng atung heeng vahang val thung
Now, when the Gmelina tree grows up,
vakowng he thabol nu ikang-ikang pho-pho akang pho-pho akang pho-pho nu
the bark of the tree becomes thick and burns with a cracking sound
it dries up and ehm that
palu to ajung tal pow nu inal ring rung
the old bark falls down and becomes smooth
kum sowru khuso danite vakowng to tumkheh
If it is too old enough, the cover again
akang pho-pho akang pho nu tal pow khunu
changes and decends to the ground and
vanu tuwng adal ahlija vada thung tuwng
when his mother said "Wake up and change"
anihin he itho ine am maso, ahli hlo-hlo idal ine am maso
there will be no dead and we will never get old
ahli hlo-hlo hin sin sung pal va hin sin de
we would change and live on.
vachapa tuwng amato da ma nu pavung ahlija vadate
But the son didn't say that and say gmelina
thing tata vapha isow ahli hlo-hlo ahli hlo hlo nu
after a long time, it peeled off
it changed into new again and again
ata tuwng etho ehring he tuwng eam vahin sin
likewise, we have dead and live among us
napi napu hin tuwng dapa nu mah
